  "original_title": "\u0da2\u0dcf\u0dad\u0dd2\u0d9a \u0d89\u0db1\u0dca\u0db0\u0db1 \u0db6\u0dbd\u0db4\u0dad\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dba \u0dc0\u0dd0\u0da9\u0dd2 \u0d89\u0db1\u0dca\u0db0\u0db1 \u0dc4\u0dbd\u0dca \u0dc3\u0d82\u0d9b\u0dca\u200d\u0dba\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0d9a \u0d9a\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dcf\u0dad\u0dca\u0db8\u0d9a\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "National fuel license is in operation at more number of fuel stations",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "According to Mr. Kanchana Wijesekera, the Minister of Electricity and Energy, yesterday (29th) saw the highest number of fuel stations that used the system in one day after the introduction of the National Fuel Licence.",
        "According to him, the number of fuel sheds that used the license system yesterday is 657. The minister also said that 962 petrol stations have adopted this system so far.",
        "The total number of operational fuel stations in Sri Lanka is 1190. Also, the number of vehicles registered in this system is 4 651 911."
      ],
